citeinfo.title: 2015 Methodology Statement: Business Locations and Business Summary
2015 Esri Business Analyst Desktop Variable and Report List

descript.abstract: Infogroup collects information on over 13 million private and public US companies. Individual businesses are located by address geocoding—not all will have an exact location. The Esri geocoder integrates an address-based approach with more than forty-five million residential and commercial U.S. address records from the Tele Atlas Address Points database. This database maps street addresses to a physical location so each address is a fixed point and not an interpolation from an address range. The geocoder uses address locators in a cascading fallback approach to ensure a match for as many records as possible. The primary locator utilizes the Navteq Address Points database. The secondary locator utilizes the Navteq Street Address Range database. Records that did not match fall back to the geocode provided by Infogroup. Businesses can be retrieved by their Standard Industrial Classification Code (SIC) as well as by North American Industry Classification System (NAICS) Code and Location. The Infogroup Business File can be used for locating both competitors and marketing opportunities. This data is current as of Feb. 2015.
descript.purpose: Infogroup Business Locations represents the locations of over 13 million private and public companies in United States. It includes address information, estimated sales or assets, number of employees, franchise/specialty information, and Standard Industrial Classification (SIC) and North American Industry Classification System (NAICS) codes.

attrdomv.udom: Sequential unique whole numbers that are automatically generated.

attr.attrdef: The street address of the location.
Four-digit extension to the primary ZIP code, if available.
Estimated sales or assets in thousands of dollars.
Whether the location is a headquarters, branch, or subsidiary headquarters.
The actual number of employees for the business.
Whether the location is a franchise or not a franchise.
A range describing the square footage of the business.
000-100: The score is a value assigned to all potential candidates of an address match.

citeinfo.title: Infogroup Business Listing File
citeinfo.othercit: Also provided the Infogroup SIC-to-NAICS crosswalk file.

procstep.srcused: Esri Business Analyst 10 Locator Update USA Geocoding Service locator with Navteq
procstep.procdesc: Received the Infogroup® Business Listing File from Infogroup Added the NAICS_EXT attribute using the values of the SIC attribute and the Infogroup SIC-to-NAICS crosswalk file. Created a lookup table with STATE and STATE_NAME attributes. Joined the table to this data set and added the STATE_NAME attribute. Converted and divided the Business Listing File into two dBASE® (.dbf) files, one with the address attributes and the other with the business attributes. Used the ArcGIS 10 Business Analyst Locator Update USA Geocoding Service locator to geocode the address attributes file. For all records with addresses that did not match to the locator's address points or street addresses, their coordinates were restored back to the original Infogroup coordinates. Coded the MATCH_CODE attribute values depending on how each record's address was geocoded. Used the coordinates in ArcGIS to create an Event Theme. Converted the Event Theme and then joined the remaining business attributes from the second dBASE file. Loaded into ArcSDE using ArcCatalog. Converted the ArcSDE layer into FGDB format using Data Development Kit Professional 2 (DDKP2). Created the projection file (.prj) and the spatial and attribute indices.
procstep.procsv: ArcGIS® 10, ArcSDE®, Data Development Kit Professional 2 (DDKP2)

dataqual.logic: The data set is converted to FGDB (File Geodatabase Feature Class) format using either Esri FGDB Data Development Kit Professional 2 (DDKP2) or tools in ArcGIS.
dataqual.complete: After processing, the data set is checked for drawing display and number of records and file sizes compared with source materials.

digtinfo.formspec: The FGDB file contains the geospatial and attribute data. The SDI file contains the spatial index. The PRJ file contains the coordinate system information (optional). The EDK file contains the license. The IDI file contains the index descriptor (optional). The <data set name>.idx folder contains the attribute indexes (optional). The XML file (*.fgdb.xml) contains the metadata describing the data set (optional).
